node.text:
Not for the faint of heart 😬

Here’s an except of the IG Live I did with @lush_rx. Watch me get cheek filler using Restylane Lyft and the new Restylane Contour - which is supposed to be the most natural look cheek filler with the most natural movement.

I’ll post before and afters soon! 

Thank you @krystal_np_injects @lush_rx for always keeping me fresh!

#restylanecontour #restylanecontour
#restylanelyft
#cheekfillers
#houstonbloggers 
#houstonblogger 
#houstonmedspa

node.title: Getting Restylane Lyft and Contour Cheek Filler with @lush_rx

How to be a Kardashian: the tutorial part 1

node.text:
#madelyncline from #Outerbanks - example of amazing work on a gorgeous person. 
When I first started watching the show, her lip fillers were obvious to me. 
Now that I’ve seen befores, her surgical nose job to thin and define the tip is as well.
She may have had other small tweaks too (undereyes, cheek filler to raise her cheek bones?)

There are also before and afters from her Charleston injector showing lips and non surgical nose job as well. 

All those little tweaks really just enhanced the beauty foundation she had naturally. Suits her face so well.. great work!!

**All befores are circa 2016-2017 professional headshots and clips from other work such as stranger things**
**All afters are 2020-2021 from red carpet pics and video stills**

He’s known to be a favorite amongst celebs and his procedures are rumored to be over $100k. 

So yeah, diligently using my sunscreen and retinol bc I will never be able to afford this 😅😅

Left is what was posted on Kyliecosmetics with the glitching, right is the fixed version on her page.

Can’t believe y’all are doubting me or even suggesting I’m providing fake receipts. 

💀

The Karjenners’ filters are glitching.
In Kim’s, you can see her fingers and her phone glitch and warp - the entire video is edited/filtered but we see it on her phone and fingers the most.

In Kylie’s, her whole face is glitching but I see it the most in her lips changing size and projection. The camera flashes are messing up the filter. THIS IS POSTED ON KYLIECOSMETICS - she reposted one without glitches on her own page 2 hours ago. 

These are so bad that I wonder if they just want attention since both of these posts are product line advertisements? 

#karjenners #kardashians #kyliejenner #kimkardashian #videoeditor #videofilter

Not for the faint of heart 😬

Here’s an except of the IG Live I did with @lush_rx. Watch me get cheek filler using Restylane Lyft and the new Restylane Contour - which is supposed to be the most natural look cheek filler with the most natural movement.

I’ll post before and afters soon! 

Thank you @krystal_np_injects @lush_rx for always keeping me fresh!

#restylanecontour #restylanecontour
#restylanelyft
#cheekfillers
#houstonbloggers 
#houstonblogger 
#houstonmedspa

Trying out the new #RestylaneContour tomorrow at @lush_rx. 

I’ll be going live tomorrow at about 10 am CST if you want to see me get cheek injections live!

node.text:
“#LiveLoveLift” - @marcjacobs 

“New York plastic surgeon Dr. Andrew Jacono performed Jacobs's “more modern” facelift using the advanced deep plane technique he's been pioneering for over 13 years, which lifts only under the muscle layer, leaving the skin attached to the muscle layers to steer clear of tightness for a smoother, softer lifted look. The surgeon sees Jacobs’s willingness to be transparent as an important step forward for openness and acceptance. “A big frustration is that people in the public eye that have means seem to be genetic mutants and make the rest of us feel like we’re not up to par," he explains. "But the truth is there's a certain point in life where you can’t fix things without surgery. The people who look good never talk about it, so it only adds to the confusion. When someone of Marc's status is sharing, it helps people realize that there are things we all can do to maintain ourselves and enhance our appearance. It sends people a message: Yes, it's possible to look like yourself, it's not as bad as you think, and you can get the results you want without looking like you had bad plastic surgery.””
